TypeGraphQL is a **server-side, code-first** approach — it solves a different problem than what `kapow-mfp` is addressing.

### What TypeGraphQL Does

Instead of writing `.graphql` SDL files and generating Go/TS code from them, you define your schema using **TypeScript classes + decorators**:

```typescript
@ObjectType()
class Institution {
  @Field()
  name: string

  @Field(() => Int)
  enrollment: number
}

@Resolver()
class InstitutionResolver {
  @Query(() => [Institution])
  async institutions(): Promise<Institution[]> { ... }
}
```

The schema is derived from the TypeScript types — single source of truth, full type safety between schema and resolvers.

### Why It Doesn't Apply to Kapow

| Aspect | TypeGraphQL | Kapow's situation |
|---|---|---|
| **Side** | Server (resolver) side | Problem is on the **client** (frontend) side |
| **Language** | TypeScript server | Kapow API is **Go** (gqlgen, schema-first) |
| **Problem solved** | Schema ↔ resolver type mismatches | Query strings ↔ schema field name mismatches |
| **Approach** | Code-first schema definition | N/A — Kapow already has schema-first working fine |

TypeGraphQL would require rewriting the Go API in TypeScript. And even then, it only ensures the **server** schema matches the **resolver** types — it doesn't help with the **client** sending queries with invalid field names (which is the bug `kapow-mfp` prevents).

The client-side problem (raw query strings referencing `menOnly`/`womenOnly` when the schema has `gender`) still needs something like gql.tada, graphql-codegen, or trusted documents regardless of what the server uses.

**Bottom line**: TypeGraphQL is irrelevant here. The gql.tada plan remains the right fit.

Sources:
- [TypeGraphQL Guide](https://www.bomberbot.com/typescript/the-ultimate-guide-to-building-type-safe-graphql-apis-with-typescript-and-typegraphql/)
- [End-to-end Type Safety with TypeScript and GraphQL](https://remi.space/blog/typescript-graphql-type-safety)
- [Schema-First vs Code-Only GraphQL](https://www.apollographql.com/blog/schema-first-vs-code-only-graphql)

